  "overview": [
    "The syllabus is divided into four sections for each class from Class 1 to Class 10, with the exception of Class 1 which has only two sections plus Achievers section.",
    "Section 1 is the basic language section; topics vary by class (e.g. Synonyms, Spellings, Collocations).",
    "Section 2 contains searching and retrieving information type questions.",
    "Section 3 contains situation-based functional English questions.",
    "Section 4 consists of Higher Order Thinking questions based on previous sections.",
    "The syllabus is class-specific and mock tests/sample papers are also provided."
